            {
              "id": 1011612,
              "key": "d4f90d54-8a74-446f-91f6-58f41f317420",
              "title": "History of Designing for Security Summary",
              "semantic_type": "TextAtom",
              "is_public": true,
              "text": "## Security in the Cloud - A Little History\n\nIn the recent past, companies and governments have adopted the cloud at a lightning fast pace.\n\nThe past few years have seen massive migrations of workloads into the public cloud and data centers are being closed and vacated right and left.\n\nMany organizations have a \"cloud first\" mandate in place for all new applications.\n\nWith the rapid adoption of the cloud, we are also seeing a rise in cloud-related security breaches.\n\nWell known brands such as Facebook, Instagram, Accenture, Verizon, and CapitalOne are just a few companies that have been affected in the last few years. The impact can be huge in dollars, impact to users, and public image. \n\nMany of these breaches were a result of weak practices around designing and configuring cloud environments. In most cases, the root cause was simple misconfiguration of cloud storage or servers, which could have been easily prevented.\n \nIn this course we will introduce you to best practices to prevent these misconfigurations and reduce the risk of a breach.",
              "instructor_notes": ""
            }
          ]
        },
