            {
              "id": 1011632,
              "key": "c793c872-a3eb-46a4-a9b1-101e43941f19",
              "title": "Course Outline Summary",
              "semantic_type": "TextAtom",
              "is_public": true,
              "text": "### Course Outline\n\nThis course focuses on architectural best practices around cloud security.\n\n#### Identity and Access Management\n\n- We will start with looking at identity and access management in AWS. \n- You will learn to secure users and roles who manage and control resources in the cloud. \n- We will also investigate best practices around authentication, authorization and fine tuning user permissions.\n\n### Securing Access to Cloud Infrastructure\n\n- We will also explore methods to ensure cloud infrastructure and networks are protected from unauthorized access. \n- This will include techniques to secure and harden access to instances and servers. \n- Additionally, we will delve into network controls offered by the cloud provider. \n- You will also get an overview of various methods to securely connect to cloud networks.\n\n\n### Data Protection in the Cloud\n\n- We will cover techniques and methods related to protecting data stored in the cloud. \n- We will leverage encryption capabilities offered by AWS. \n- Finally, we will demonstrate best practices for encryption key management.\n\n### Defensive Security in the Cloud\n\nWe will tie this all together by looking at how to incorporate security in your cloud operational model. \n- We will monitor systems to discover risks early on.\n- We will use tools to discover vulnerabilities and insecure configurations.\n- We will also review some of the AWS cloud services which can defend web applications from external threats.",
              "instructor_notes": ""
            }
          ]
        },
